title: The copie of a letter sent from sea by a gentleman who was employed in discouerie on the coast of Spaine by appointment of the generals of our English fleete, to a worshipfull friend of his. Aduertising him of such things as he came to knowledge of in the same discouerie.
author: T. F.
publisher: By Richard Field dwelling in the Blacke Friers,
notes: Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
